<paragraph id="A39F639829319F1E59AC022630D8CED2" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">SOUTH KOREA: Jeollabuk-do, Gyeongsangnam-do.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="258FBA7D73455F871B63049C8FF960D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="1F7C8EB8F2BF2DD3AB593429B9FD47E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A0E0D7D5281C29BDAEB339E84D82F59" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">The plants inhabit mountain ridges and slopes at altitudes over 800 m above sea level. Flowering specimens have been collected from June to August; fruiting specimens have been collected from October. Honeybees are frequent visitors to the flowers, suggesting that they are pollinators of the variety.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
